In a joint statement at the White House, President Trump and Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi expressed their commitment to strengthening the relationship between the United States and India. Trump praised India's accomplishments, including its fast-growing economy and its efforts to improve infrastructure and fight corruption. He also highlighted the importance of reducing the trade deficit between the two countries and increasing American exports to India. Both leaders expressed their commitment to fighting terrorism and discussed the security challenges in Afghanistan and the Indo-Pacific region. They also discussed enhancing defense and security cooperation, as well as cooperation in areas such as technology and innovation. Prime Minister Modi invited Trump's daughter, Ivanka, to lead the U.S. delegation to the Global Entrepreneurship Summit in India. The visit concluded with an invitation for Trump to visit India.